longBusinessSummary: Harte Gold Corp. engages in the acquisition, exploration, evaluation, development, and mining of mineral resource properties in Canada. The company explores for gold deposits. The company primarily focuses on its 100% owned Sugar Zone property, which consists of 69 boundary cell claims, 43 single cell claims, 197 multi-cell claims, and four mining leases covering an area of approximately 81,287 hectares located in the Sault Ste. Marie Mining Division in Ontario. The company was formerly known as Harte Resources Company and changed its name to Harte Gold Corp. in December 2003. Harte Gold Corp. was incorporated in 1982 and is headquartered in Toronto, Canada.
